title: CBT Nuggets Juniper JNCIA JN0-102
description:
This Juniper Networks video training course with Scott Morris covers the foundational information needed to start your Juniper career and certification path.

Recommended skills:

    Basic networking concepts will be covered, but Juniper Networks sets the starting bar a little higher than other vendors. So there may be a lot of view and review of content if it is all new.


Recommended equipment:

    Any Juniper Networks JUNOS device (SRX Routers and EX Switches are the most readily available candidates).
    May also access JunosSphere virtualized environments through Juniper Networks website/partners (note: there may be charges for this)


Related certifications:

    JNCIA-JUNOS (this is the beginning step and pre-requisite for all other Juniper certifications, regardless of track)


Related job functions:

    Network engineering
    Network administration
